    "body": "### Problem\n\nVim's global marks are really useful to jump around to different files. However because marks are a single, global resource, if 2+ plugins accidentally used the `A` mark, they could accidentally break each other's behavior. Because of that, plugins tend to have to maintain separate save / restore mechanisms to minimize the possibility of overlap.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAllow namespaced marks, similar to namespaced extmark. Then plugin foo could use the foo:A mark and plugin bar could use the bar:A mark safely without accidentally stepping over each other. It'd also then be possible for a single plugin to define and manage multiple namespaces at once if they choose to.",
